        },
        {
          "type": "text_block",
          "settings": {
            "text_content": "<p><strong>What if a whiter smile could fit into the time it takes to do your makeup?</strong></p><p>I used to think whiter teeth meant the dentist's chair. I'd paid for in-chair whitening more than once: $600 plus a visit, a couple of hours sitting still, and days of sensitivity afterwards. Every hot or cold drink was a reminder.</p><p>I tried the supermarket strips too. They slipped around, they were fiddly, and for me they stung.</p><p>So my teeth went back to how they were, and I went back to hiding them in photos.</p><p><strong>Then a friend showed me how she was doing it at home.</strong></p><p>She had three simple things on the bathroom shelf. A purple mouthwash she rinsed for about 30 seconds each morning for instant brightness. Enamel-safe whitening strips that actually stayed put. And a U-shaped LED device she wore hands-free while she got ready. All gentle, all alcohol-free, no sting.</p><p>For less than one in-chair visit, I could own the routine and simply reorder the strips and mouthwash. Three days later, mine arrived.</p>",
            "text_font_size": 16,
            "text_color": "#000000",
            "text_alignment": "left",
