            "divider_alignment": "center",
            "margin_top": 30,
            "margin_bottom": 30
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "article_heading",
          "settings": {
            "heading_text": "<p>Why a subscription, not a one-off?</p>",
            "heading_font_size": 26,
            "text_alignment": "left",
            "margin_top": 0,
            "margin_bottom": 16
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "text_block",
          "settings": {
            "text_content": "<p>Whitening is not a one-and-done thing, stains come back with coffee, tea, wine and time. So the routine is built around easy refills, not a big one-off purchase.</p><p>You start with the device and your first mouthwash and strips. After that, your refill of mouthwash and strips arrives on a subscribe and save plan for $29, at about the rate you actually use it. That prices the device itself at an effective $20, because most of what you pay over time is simply the refills.</p><p>There is no lock-in. You can skip, pause, change quantity or cancel from your account in a couple of clicks, no emails, no phone calls.</p>",
            "text_font_size": 16,
            "text_color": "#000000",
