        {
          "type": "text_block",
          "settings": {
            "text_content": "<p><strong>Whitening strips:</strong> Ordinary strips can work, but many slip around and sting, and they are fiddly to keep on for the contact time they need.</p><p><strong>In-chair whitening:</strong> Effective, but it is $600 or more a visit, time in the chair, and often days of sensitivity afterwards.</p><p><strong>Cheap LED kits:</strong> The light is the easy part. Without decent whitening and a device that actually holds, you are mostly buying a blue night light.</p><p><strong>Elaren:</strong> Alcohol-free purple mouthwash, enamel-safe strips, and a hands-free LED device. Refills arrive on their own, and you can skip, pause or cancel in 2 clicks.</p>",
